int fib(int n) {
    if (n < 0) {
        std::cout << "Incorrect input";
    } else if (n == 0 || n == 1) {
        return n;
    } else {
        return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2);
    }
}

int main() {
    int n;
    std::cout << "Enter n: ";
    std::cin >> n;
    std::cout << "The " << n << "th Fibonacci number is " << fib(n);
}
```

This program defines a recursive fib() function to calculate the nth Fibonacci number. The base cases are fib(0) = 0 and fib(1) = 1. For any other input n, we recursively call fib(n-1) and fib(n-2) and add the results.

